One ingredient Dulce de Leche!!

The best go to hostess gift for the holidays! Perfect in these adorable @ballcanning jars wrapped with a gorgeous satin ribbon 🎄 

Amazing on ice cream, dipping fruit and even over cheesecake! So many options 

Method: 
Pour @eaglebrandmilk sweetened  condensed milk into mini @ballcanning jars and screw on their lids. Place them in your slow cooker and add water until they just cover the lids of the jars. Put the lid on and cook on low for 6-8 hours. Perfect every time!! 

You’re welcome 🤗

Crowd favorite!!🎄 If you need me I’ll be watching Xmas movies continuously, drinking hot cocoa with mounds of marshmallows and making these gorgeous candles with my two little elves 🎄❤️

I make this beeswax candles every year. We burn them at home and give them as gifts and everyone loves them!! 

Tip: always burn down your candles at home before guests arrive. They look so beautiful if the beeswax has burned down a little. 

Items needed:
Beeswax sheets 
Strand of wick 
Scissors
Hairdryer - YES hairdryer! 
Your favorite ribbon 

Method: 
Cut your beeswax sheet to whatever height you would like. 

Cut your wick to the same length plus about an inch for it to stick out to start the burn.

Place the wick at the edge of your beeswax and start rolling gently until the desired thickness. Cut off any excess if you are doing a thinner taper. 

Take your hairdryer and on low slightly warm the edge of the beeswax and then gently press smooth out the edge of wax so it blends into the candle. 

Then either enjoy burning them in your own home or package them with a ribbon as a great little gift. 

Bonus they have no toxic fragrance chemicals, you can buy any color beeswax sheet online with the wick and they are easy for the kiddos to help out with! 

Happy Christmas Eve - Eve!! ❤️🎅🏻🤶

Homemade Eggnog 🎄or spiced eggnog if you like 😉

Comin’ at ya with a Simple Eggnog recipe that you’ll definitely want to save! This is a tradition in my family. The rich smell of eggnog cooking is so nostalgic … 

Ingredients:

6 eggs
3 cups whole milk (best with whole milk)
8 TBS of sugar 
3 tsp Pure Vanilla extract 
1/4 tsp Nutmeg

Method:

Beat the eggs with a mixer, gradually add milk and sugar until mixture is slightly thickened. 

Set your burner on the lowest setting and heat until mixture is thick enough to coat the back of a spoon. Be patient! 

Next add in your vanilla and nutmeg and stir. Take off the heat, cover with saran wrap and refrigerate until chilled 

Want a simple way to spice up your eggnog (store bought or homemade)?!

1 1/2 ounces of spiced rum per every
 4 ounces of eggnog. Top each glass off with a pinch of cinnamon or nutmeg!

Merry Christmas Eve ❤️🎄

Healthy smoothie recipe … keeping it simple with this easy recipe … 

continuing on my 100 day challenge and finding new ways to have healthy alternatives … but this one is an oldie but goodie! 

Ingredients: 
1c almond milk
1/2c Greek vanilla yogurt nonfat
1/2c frozen mixed berries
Handful of raw baby spinach
*you can add protein powder if you want to*

Method:

Blend it all together and pour into your favorite glass. Enjoy! 

Calories 160
Protein 12g
Fat 2.5g
Carbs 20g

Sunday 🤍

DIY window seat cushion complete! 

Sometimes you just have to dig in and do things yourself. Am I right? We built the window seat so when we were quoted $790 for the seat cushion I thought why not do the cushion to?! 

I typically like down wrapped everything. Sofa cushions, down inserts for throw pillows … all of it. But I felt like this needed to be more solid and it’s perfect! 

Total cost $172 and bought all the material at our local @joann_stores  It took only a couple hours of work! I couldn’t be happier 👏👏

Country queen 🐓

Love my walks especially in the early morning when we walk a little farther out. It’s quiet and it’s just me, the fresh air and farm animals. 

I’ve incorporated more low intensity cardio into my wellness journey and it’s a game changer. Long walks and consistently hitting that 10k steps a day mark has made a big difference! I’ve noticed it’s all the little consistent things like hydration, walking and clean eating that have really made the big differences. 

So get moving people!! Get some fresh air, get some steps in and enjoy a slower pace sometimes!
Cozy holiday vibes 🎄🎅🏻❤️
